    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-11-03T19:22:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-11-03T19:22:00-05:00" n="310"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <head>310. Telegram 201141 From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d310fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, <gloss
                            target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> (<gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss>) 9
                        INDIA. Confidential; Immediate. Drafted on November 3 by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SDT1">Schneider</persName>; cleared in the Office of
                        International Finance and Development of the Bureau of Economic and Business
                        Affairs by John Gervers, and in the Office of Planning and Development of
                            <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>’s Bureau for Asia by Alfred D.
                        White; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_MAH1">Meyer</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d310fn2">The U.S. agreed to participate with
                        the other members of the India Consortium in restructuring India’s foreign
                        debt.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1972-11-04T00:22:00+00:00">November 4, 1972, 0022Z</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subj:</head>
                    <item>Indian Debt Rescheduling</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> has decided to participate for one year
                        rpt one year in World Bank proposal for debt relief for India with <gloss
                            target="#t_US1">US</gloss> share of $29.12 million.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>We have informed World Bank of this decision as part of our continuing
                        technical discussions with bank. Bank is informing Indians and other
                        AID-India Consortium members.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Pending further guidance Embassy should avoid any interpretive comment
                        regarding this decision in discussions with Indian officials. Embassy should
                        not rpt not issue press statement and should restrict response to possible
                        press queries to simple confirmation that decision made.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
